               <interp inst="t17471209-25" type="year" value="1747"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17471209-25" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17471209"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17471209-25" type="date" value="17471209"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17471209-25-off114-c172" targOrder="Y" targets="t17471209-25-defend221 t17471209-25-off114 t17471209-25-verdict117"></join>
         
               <p>30. 
               
                  <persName id="t17471209-25-defend221" type="defendantName">
                     James 
                     Fitzsimons 
                  <interp inst="t17471209-25-defend221" type="surname" value="Fitzsimons"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-defend221" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-defend221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17471209-25-off114" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-off114" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-off114" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing three pounds weight of sugar, value 18 d. the goods of persons unknown
            </rs>, <rs id="t17471209-25-cd115" type="crimeDate">Dec. 3</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17471209-25-off114 t17471209-25-cd115"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17471209-25-person222">
                  Philip 
                  Breading 
               <interp inst="t17471209-25-person222" type="surname" value="Breading"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-person222" type="given" value="Philip"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-person222" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The Prisoner was a <rs id="t17471209-25-deflabel116" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17471209-25-defend221 t17471209-25-deflabel116"></join> on board of my ship that was laden from Jamaica with rum and sugar, I helpt to take the sugar out of the lining of his breeches.</p>
               <p>Q. What did the Prisoner say?</p>
               <p>Breading. He did not think any harm in it; the same day I cut his pocket off with a pound of sugar.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17471209-25-person223">
                  Thomas 
                  Wesbrook 
               <interp inst="t17471209-25-person223" type="surname" value="Wesbrook"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-person223" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-person223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The 4th of December I detected him in the morning with stuffing a lump of sugar in his pocket, after that the Captain called them all down to the hold, to work upon logwood, being too wet that day to work the sugar, and I found three pounds and a half upon him at four o'clock.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17471209-25-verdict117" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-verdict117" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-verdict117" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17471209-25-punish118" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17471209-25-punish118" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17471209-25-defend221 t17471209-25-punish118"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
